  "release_note_excerpt": "# Release Notes: Codex Runtime Security Prototype\n\n## Release Name\n\nCodex Runtime Security Prototype\n\n## Completed Stages\n\n1. Static-only Codex scan.\n2. Dynamic evidence integration.\n3. Safe Docker sandbox smoke.\n4. Runtime monitor and kill path.\n5. Sandbox hardening roadmap.\n6. Egress proxy / allowlist design.\n7. Syscall policy classification.\n8. Policy-driven enforcement regression.\n9. Evidence schema.\n10. Synthetic attack matrix.\n11. Release freeze / safe regression suite.\n12. CI/CD safe regression integration draft.\n13. Offline dashboard / visual report.\n\n## Verified Safety Boundary\n\n- No real malicious samples were executed.\n- No real tokens were passed.\n- No real `~/.codex`, `~/.agents`, `.env`, or SSH key material was read.\n- Docker runtime design defaults to `--network none`.\n- `--privileged` is forbidden.\n- `docker.sock` is not mounted.\n- Network access is not opened by the regression suite.\n- This is a research prototype, not a production system.\n\n## Key Evidence\n\n- `safe_skill`-only enforce smoke: `HIGH=0`, `CRITICAL=0`, expected timeout under `--network none`.\n- Synthetic kill path: `container_killed_by_monitor=true`.\n- Policy-driven enforcement regression: `fake_kill_called=true`.\n- Synthetic attack matrix: 10 cases passed.",
